 protest over alleged non-payment of allowances and exclusion from the  amnesty programme. September 18, 2018 In "News" Hundreds of ex-militants, yesterday in Benin City, Edo State, staged a peaceful protest over alleged non-payment of their 18 months’ allowances. They called on President Goodluck Jonathan to immediately remove his Special Adviser on Niger Delta Matters, Mr. Kingsely Kuku. July 31, 2012 In "News" Motorists plying the East-West Road were, yesterday, stranded for hours as ex-Niger Delta militants under the Federal Government's amnesty programme blocked the road in protest over alleged non-payment of their arrears. December 19, 2014 In "News"